<h1>Facets and Filters</h1>
        
<div class=WordSection1>
<p><b>What are facets? </b></p>

<p>Facets are a technique for filtering information organized
according to the available facet classification.</p>

<p><b>How can I use facets?</b></p>

<p>You can use facets by clicking on the facet available in the
left hand column to limit your search results to the particular facet selected.</p>

<p><b>Can I combine filters?</b></p>

<p>Yes. The filters are designed to use an "or" function with-in a filter and an "and" function between filters.</p>

<p><b>What kinds of facets are available for me?</b></p>

<p><b>Location Filter:</b></p>

<p>The location filter will limit your search results to the
library locations selected. The
user can limit the search results to more than one location.</p>

<p>The digital collection will limit the search results to all
e-material for example eBooks. </p>

<p><b>Material Type:</b></p>

<p>The Material type filter will limit your search results to the material type selected. For example DVD or Blu-Ray. The user can limit the search results to more than one material type at once.</p>

<p>The Material types hierarchy allows you to select a material type group and by doing so you select all material type under that group. For example if you select images it will select both print image and digital image material types.</p>

